South Africa has recorded 903 new coronavirus infections for a second day in a row. The total number of COVID-19 cases now stands at 672 572. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 29 September. Use the COVID Alert SA app to protect yourself, your loved ones and your community. Start using this privacy preserving app today. Add your phone to the fight! Download the Covid Alert SA app now! https://t.co/8YKEqaiiRF pic.twitter.com/jmzJabrQZa — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) September 29, 2020  There has been 81 new fatalities overnight, taking the death toll to 16 666. The Eastern Cape and the North West recorded 8 deaths respectively, Gauteng 28, the Northern Cape 10; 11 in KwaZulu-Natal, five in Limpopo and the Free State, and six in the Western Cape. The country’s recovery rate remains at 90% with 606 520 South Africans having survived the disease.  